http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/Home-Minister-sees-no-stringent-remarks/article14017145.ece

Home Minister Ramesh Chennithala has described as baseless reports that the Thrissur Vigilance court has passed stringent remarks about the Vigilance Department while ordering a probe into the allegations against K. Babu on Saturday.The Minister said in a statement here that the court has only ordered to register an FIR and probe the case under its supervision. No complaints or criticism have been made against the Vigilance or its functioning. The Vigilance had not given a final opinion completing quick verification and whether a case should be registered in the complaint which came up before the court, he said. The Vigilance had only sought more time for completing the probe, he said.